pieces
25 tiles. Player 1 (P1) has red, Player 2 (P2) has
blue. The white tiles are shared between them.
rules
Begin with white tile crossing 4 sides. Players
take turns adding tiles (theirs or a neutral one)
to the board. The tile must connect correctly
and must keep the knot in a 5x5 area. If a player
can not move, they pass.
The game ends when no player can move -
either all tiles have been used or all knots clased.
scores
The player with the highest knot score wins.
The knot score is the number of a players tiles
visited by a single knot.
A game by Cameron Browne.
notes
If a player makes an illegal move, they take the
tile back and forfeit their turn.
The starting square does not have to be the
center of the 5x5.
Players scores can, but do not have to come
from the same knot.
